                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <p>Vellum, about 10 in. by 6 7/8, consisting of 25
                                    leaves, some of which, are much stained and torn,
                                    especially <locus>foll. 14</locus>, <locus>16</locus>, and <locus>17</locus>. The volume
                                    originally consisted of at least five quires, the
                                    first two of which were lost at a comparatively
                                    early period. They are signed with letters. Leaves
                                    are wanting after <locus>foll. 11</locus> and <locus>19</locus>. Each page has
                                    from 31 to 36 lines.</p>
                            </item>
                        </list>
